This document describes the modules and functions of the Sequencer24
application.

\mainpage   Sequencer24
\author     Chris Ahlstrom 2015-09-05

\section seq24_reference_intro Introduction

Sequencer24 is a minor cleanup, refactoring, and documentation of the
Seq24 live-play MIDI sequencer.

The current document describes the functions, classes, modules, and other
entities used in this project.

For now, please read the ROADMAP and README files to understand the genesis
of this project.

Also, we have pretty deeply documented <i>Seq24</i> and <i>Sequencer24</i>
with PDF files that can be
generated by git-cloning the following projects, installing a number of tools
related to PDF and LaTeX, and running "make":

   -  https://github.com/ahlstromcj/seq24-doc.git
   -  https://github.com/ahlstromcj/sequencer24-doc.git

In the present document, we've left out a fair amount of side-material to cut
down on the size of the document.  For example, the main module, redundant
Windows support, utility headers like easy_macros.h, simple stuff like the
mutex module, the fruity variants (at least the ones already refactored into
their own modules), etc., are all left out.

